      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-conditions-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation data were collected at 5 operating points. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) was used rather than porcine or human blood, and temperature was controlled to 22°C rather than physiological 37°C. These deviations introduce systematic differences in viscosity and red blood cell fragility that are not corrected in the hemolysis model. Achieved level 2 reflects partial but non-physiological test condition fidelity."
