      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is known to have limited validity outside its original calibration range. No formal model form uncertainty analysis, alternative model comparison, or Bayesian model selection was performed to characterize structural model error. This is the most critical gap identified: model form uncertainty is unquantified for the primary prediction quantity. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
